&lt;h2&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pelican:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
pip install pelican
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ghp-import:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
pip install ghp-import
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="creating-github-pages"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Creating GitHub Pages&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol class="arabic simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create GitHub account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate SSH Key and register it (optional. otherwise, use https)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create username.github.io repository as a User Page&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="creating-and-initializing-working-directory"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Creating and initializing working directory&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;mkdir workdir&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="go"&gt;cd workdir&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="go"&gt;git init&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="go"&gt;git remote add origin git@github.com:username/username.github.io.git&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="working-with-pelican"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Working with Pelican&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To launch server and allow automatic html generation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
make devserver
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This starts pelican and http.server processes on background.
To stop them:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
./develop_server.sh stop
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To publish to GitHub:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
make github
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See Makefile.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
